    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hammers used by farriers to shoe horses. Most often these feature compact solid metal heads with a flattened face on one end of the head for driving nails, and curved forked tines on the other end for pulling out nails.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
